          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Average flux for  587 days irradiation",
                "   ('Long term'): 1.093 x 10**14 +- 3% n/cm2/s.",
                "      Average flux for  19.6 days irradiation",
                "   ('Short term'): 1.805 x 10**14 +- 5% n/cm2/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thermal Maxwellian flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 2 mg of meteoritic manganese extracted from about",
                " 20 grams of the iron meteorite \"Duchesne\" and",
                " containing 6.5 dpm 53Mn were purified by paper chroma-",
                " tography, ashed and dissolved in dilute HN03 + H202.",
                " The Mn solution was then homogenized with 2.3 mg of",
                " high purity ZnO (65Zn as internal standard) and",
                " 285 mg MgO.",
                " The composition of the meteoritic Mn-samples:",
                " 'Long term' irradiation:",
                " 53Mn - 0.00019 mu-g; 55Mn - 230.5 mu-g;",
                " Zn - 216.0 mu-g; Mg - 19.70 mg",
                "  'Short term' irradiation:",
                " 53Mn - 0.000208 mu-g; 55Mn - 253.3 mu-g;",
                " Zn - 237.4 mu-g; Mg - 21.65 mg.",
                " Amounts of each 35 mg oxide-mixture were enclosed in",
                " quartz ampoules (diam. = 6 mm; 25 mm long). Two of",
                " these ampoules were used for the 'Long' term reactor",
                " irradiation, a third one for the short (20 d)",
                " irradiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The 54.Mn was counted in a NaI(TI) detector",
                " 2 x 2 inch. by its 0.835 MeV-gamma-line. The yield of",
                " 55Mn was determined by neutron activation via 56Mn by",
                " its 0.847 keV-line.",
                " The 65Zn activity was determined by its",
                " 1.12 MeV-gamma-line in a large distance of 33 cm by a",
                " 2 x 2 inch NaI(TI) detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In order to increase the security, aliquots were",
                "counted with a 30 cc Ge(Li)detector independently.",
                "The Mn and Fe standards were treated in the same way."
              ]
            }
          ],
